FT  13 MAY 92 / Letter: No remit for back-door advertising
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr CHRIS GRAYLING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, l would like to clarify one area raised by Raymond Snoddy in his
comprehensive feature (Management: Marketing and Advertising, 'Turning to
television for the power and the glory', May 7) about the broadcasting of
company annual general meetings on BBC Select.
While the BBC believes that improving shareholder access to company
information is perfectly in keeping with its public service remit, it is
also important to ensure that the service does not allow advertising by the
back door. So any mention of products on the new service must be clearly
within the context of the meeting, and must not be promotional in tone.
The use of BBC airtime to cover events such as product launches will not be
permitted.
Chris Grayling,
commissioning editor,
BBC Select,
80 Wood Lane, London W12
