<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 92 / Time targets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Rail yesterday published the first figures to show its performance
against targets on a line-by-line basis since the Passenger's Charter was
introduced two months ago. The chart shows how four of the 15 Network
SouthEast routes and five out of the seven InterCity routes are missing the
punctuality targets in the BR Passenger's Charter. Regional Railways, the
provincial network, is doing rather better: only two of its 22 routes (Cross
Country and East and West Midlands) are failing to meet the required
standard.
Under the Passenger's Charter, regular rail customers will receive discounts
on season ticket renewals if their lines fail to meet performance targets by
more than a narrow margin over a 12-month period.
