FT  12 MAY 92 / Travel agents dubbed 'lazy'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN THORNHILL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MANY TRAVEL agents are 'incompetent and lazy' and waste money by making
basic errors, according to a report from Which?, the Consumers' Association
magazine, published today, John Thornhill writes.
The magazine says more than half its inquiries to 253 travel agents in 10
cities were handled badly, with agents telling half-truths and quoting
unnecessarily high fares.
Only one in five agents was able to find the cheapest routine flight to Nice
 -a Pounds 129 offer from British Airways. Which? says Hogg Robinson
provided the best service of the five big travel chains.
