Seasonally adjusted data used in all cases. Statistics for Germany apply
only to western Germany.  GNP/GDP is broken down into private
consumption expenditure, investment (the sum of gross fixed capital
formation and the change in stocks), general government final
consumption, and net exports (exports of goods and services minus
imports of goods and services). The US includes investment by government
in the government series rather than under investment. Quarterly GNP/GDP
totals are annualised. The growth rates are the percentage change over
the corresponding period in the previous year, and are positive unless
otherwise stated. The figures in the fifth column of each set of growth
rates refer only to exports, rather than to net exports. Data supplied
by Datastream and WEFA from national government sources.
